becker.robots
Class Directions

java.lang.Object
  becker.robots.Directions

public abstract class Directions
extends Object

Constants which define directions in the robot city. The constants have the following properties:

  • The values of adjacent directions in {EAST, SOUTH, WEST, NORTH} differ by 2 (mod 8).
  • Values increase in the clockwise direction (e.g.: SOUTH > EAST).
  • The directions in {SOUTHEAST, SOUTHWEST, NORTHWEST, NORTHEAST} are used to specify parts of an IntersectionIcon.
This class exists only for the constants it provides and is not meant to be instantiated.

Author:
Byron Weber Becker

DIRECTION_NAMES

public static final String[] DIRECTION_NAMES
An array of direction name strings. Example: Directions.DIRECTION_NAMES[Directions.NORTHWEST] will yield "Northwest".

OPPOSITE_DIRECTION

public static final int[] OPPOSITE_DIRECTION
An array giving the direction which is opposite the direction used as an index. For example, Directions.OPPOSITE_DIRECTION[Directions.NORTH] yields Directions.SOUTH.
